Czech supplier of coal to steelmakers, fell for the first time
in four days as the price of the commodity declined.  NWR dropped 2.1 percent to 153.76 koruna by 12:06 p.m. in
 Prague , snapping a 4.6 percent advance in the previous three
sessions.  Europe â€™s benchmark coal futures  contracts  slid 1
